# Spacing

At our design system, we use an 8px baseline grid to ensure consistent and harmonious layouts across all our digital products. This means that we base our spacing values on multiples of 8 pixels.

## Tokens

Each spacing element is defined as a token, which is a pre-determined value that represents a specific spacing distance. These tokens help ensure consistency and simplify the design process. Here are the spacing tokens we use:

| token | rem | px | example | 
|-------|-----|----|---------| 
| $ifxSpace12 | 0.0625 | 1 | <img src={Space12} alt="Spacing 1px" width="50%" /> | 
| $ifxSpace25 | 0.125 | 2 | <img src={Space25} alt="Spacing 2px" width="50%" /> | 
| $ifxSpace50 | 0.25 | 4 | <img src={Space50} alt="Spacing 4px" width="50%" /> | 
| $ifxSpace100 |0.5 | 8 | <img src={Space100} alt="Spacing 8px" width="50%" /> | 
| $ifxSpace150 | 0.75 | 12 | <img src={Space150} alt="Spacing 12px" width="50%" /> | 
| $ifxSpace200 | 1 | 16 | <img src={Space200} alt="Spacing 16px" width="50%" /> | 
| $ifxSpace250 | 1.25 | 20 | <img src={Space250} alt="Spacing 20px" width="50%" /> | 
| $ifxSpace300 | 1.5 | 24 | <img src={Space300} alt="Spacing 24px" width="50%" /> | 
| $ifxSpace400 | 2 | 32 | <img src={Space400} alt="Spacing 32px" width="50%" /> | 
| $ifxSpace500 | 2.5 | 40 | <img src={Space500} alt="Spacing 40px" width="50%" /> | 
| $ifxSpace600 | 3 | 48 | <img src={Space600} alt="Spacing 48px" width="50%" /> | 
| $ifxSpace700 | 3,5 | 56 | <img src={Space700} alt="Spacing 56px" width="50%" /> | 
| $ifxSpace800 | 4 | 64 | <img src={Space800} alt="Spacing 64px" width="50%" /> | 
| $ifxSpace900 | 4.5 | 72 | <img src={Space900} alt="Spacing 72px" width="50%" /> | 
| $ifxSpace1000 | 5 | 80 | <img src={Space1000} alt="Spacing 80px" width="50%" /> | 
| $ifxSpace1100 | 5.5 | 88 | <img src={Space1100} alt="Spacing 88px" width="50%" /> | 
